thread.title: University of Mobile volleyball players Jessica Bagwell and Bailey Nations earn SSAC weekly honors
thread.title_full: University of Mobile volleyball players Jessica Bagwell and Bailey Nations earn SSAC weekly honors | AL.com

author: UMobile Athletics
title: University of Mobile volleyball players Jessica Bagwell and Bailey Nations earn SSAC weekly honors
text:
The University of Mobile's Bailey Nations and Jessica Bagwell were named SSAC Volleyball Attacker and Defender of the Week, respectively. The awards are for the week of Sept. 28 – Oct. 4.
This is Bagwell's second such honor this year, while Nations was previously named SSAC Volleyball Player of the Week each of the previous two seasons.
Bailey Nations – SR – OH – Peoria, Ariz.
• Totaled 26 kills (3.71 k/s) and 11 digs (1.57 d/s)
• Hit .418 with only three attack errors
• 10 kills v. Loyola and 16 kills in a four-set win over Xavier
• Ranks 3rd in the SSAC in hitting percentage and kills/set
Jessica Bagwell – JR – L – Cordova, Ala.
• Totaled an impressive 44 digs for an average of 6.29 digs/set
• 20 digs v. Loyola and 24 digs v. Xavier
• Only 1 reception error in 43 attempts
• Averages 4.6 digs/set, which would be a school record
Additional Notes
• Mobile is 16-2 on the season and 5-1 in SSAC action
• Lady Rams host Brewton-Parker Friday at 7:30 p.m. and Coastal Georgia Saturday at 1 p.m.
• Mobile has totaled four volleyball weekly honors this year
